OL,6,FSpeaking to journalists after First
OL,7,FMinister's Questions, Mr Matheson
OL,8,Finsisted he will stay on as an MSP,
OL,9,Fadding: "I think it's pretty clear
OL,10,Fthat the process has become highly
OL,11,Fpoliticised, which has compromised the
OL,12,Fprocess and the fairness of the
OL,13,Fprocess.J"I also think the sanctions
OL,14,Fthey've imposed are excessive and they
OL,15,Fare unfair."JMr Matheson said it is
OL,16,Fnow for Parliament to decide on the
OL,17,Fnext steps, and he vowed to "abide" by
OL,18,Fwhatever decision it takes. He said he
OL,19,Fhopes he will continue to represent
OL,20,FFalkirk West "for many years to come".
