OL,6,FBut Scottish Tory leader Douglas Ross
OL,7,Faccused Mr Matheson of "deceit and
OL,8,Fabuse of trust" as he revealed his
OL,9,Fparty will seek to push him to resign
OL,10,Fin a vote next week.JHe described Mr
OL,11,FSwinney's support for his SNP
OL,12,Fcolleague as "incredible and
OL,13,Findefensible". Rather than being a
OL,14,F"First Minister for all of Scotland"
OL,15,Fas he claimed after taking the role,
OL,16,FMr Ross described him as a "First
OL,17,FMinister that backs his pals".
