OL,6,FWhile it has no doubt increased
OL,7,Fpressure on him to stand down as an
OL,8,FMSP, he may stay on, given the
OL,9,FScottish Parliament has no way of
OL,10,Fremoving elected members in the way
OL,11,Fthe UK Parliament does.
OL,13,FSouth of the border, a suspension of
OL,14,F10 sitting days is enough to spark a
OL,15,Frecall petition, which allows
OL,16,Fconstituents to remove an MP if 10%
OL,17,Fsign the document.
